{"article_id":"ruS0GVFGdOMHxXgA","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"CAYCE , S.C.","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"( ) -","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"( This Feb. 4 story corrects first paragraph","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"to drop erroneous reference to three fatal crashes in as many months .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"Amtrak has had four fatal crashes since December .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"The error first occurred in UPDATE 3 of the Feb. 4 story )","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"An Amtrak passenger train","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"that was diverted onto a side track","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"slammed into a parked freight train in South Carolina on Sunday ,","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"killing two crew members","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"and injuring at least 116 others in the railroad ' s fourth fatal crash since December .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Amtrak Train 91 ,","depth":13},{"id":12,"text":"carrying nine crew members and 136 passengers ,","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"was traveling from New York to Miami","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"when it hit the CSX Corp freight train","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"that was stopped on a side track , or siding ,","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"at about 2:35 a.m. local time","depth":13},{"id":17,"text":"( 0735 GMT ) .","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"The section of track was operated by CSX","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"and the Amtrak train was diverted onto the siding at a switch","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"where a padlock had been attached","depth":14},{"id":21,"text":"to steer train traffic that way ,","depth":14},{"id":22,"text":"Robert Sumwalt , chairman of the U.S. National Transportation Board , told a news conference .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"\" Key to this investigation is learning","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"why the switch was lined that way , \"","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"he said ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"calling the damage to the locomotives \" catastrophic. \"","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"An NTSB investigation team was at the site .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Amtrak engineer Michael Kempf , 54 , of Savannah , Georgia , and conductor Michael Cella , 36 , of Orange Park , Florida , were killed ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Lexington County Coroner Margaret Fisher told reporters .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"Autopsies were underway ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Two of the 116 people injured were in critical condition after the wreck ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"which occurred about 5 miles","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"( 8 km )","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"southwest of the state capital Columbia .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"\" It ' s a horrible thing","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"to see ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"to understand what force was involved , \"","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"South Carolina Governor Henry McMaster told reporters .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"\" The first engine of the freight train was torn up ,","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"and the single engine of the passenger train is barely recognizable . \"","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Amtrak said","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"it was \" deeply saddened \" by the deaths .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"It said","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"CSX owns and controls the dispatching of all trains ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"including the signal systems","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"that control access to sidings and yards ,","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"Amtrak said in a statement .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Amtrak President and CEO Richard Anderson said","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"the passenger train hit the tail end of the CSX train .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"That train had two locomotives and 34 empty auto racks","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"used to transport cars ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"the NTSB said .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"The passenger train ' s locomotive was left lying on its side ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"and the first car was bent and also derailed ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"although it remained upright ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"images from the scene showed .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Emergency responders are at the scene","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"after an Amtrak passenger train collided with a freight train","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"and derailed in Cayce , South Carolina , U.S. , February 4 , 2018 .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"/Randall Hill","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"At least four of the freight train ' s cars were crumpled ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"looking like crushed tin foil ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"but remained on the tracks .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"The passenger train was part of Amtrak ' Silver Star Service .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"Officials said","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"some 5,000 gallons of fuel leaked","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"as a result of the collision ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"but that there was no threat to public safety .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"U.S. President Donald Trump received regular updates on the crash","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"while at his resort in Palm Beach , Florida .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"\" My thoughts and prayers are with all of the victims","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"involved in this mornings","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"( sic )","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"train collision in South Carolina , \"","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"\" Thank you to our incredible First Responders","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"for the work","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"they ' ve done ! \"","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"McMaster said","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"he had been told the Amtrak train was traveling at about 59 miles","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"( 95 km )","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"per hour upon impact .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"The NTSB did not release details on the speed","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"at which the Amtrak train was traveling .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"In December , three people were killed","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"when an Amtrak passenger train derailed in Washington state .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"The engineer later told the NTSB","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"he had misread a signal","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"and tried to brake before the accident .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"In late January , an Amtrak train","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"carrying Republican members of the U.S. Congress","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"killed one person in a garbage truck","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"with which it collided in Virginia .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"A Federal Railroad Administration Investigative team was also on the scene in South Carolina","depth":3},{"id":96,"text":"to help establish what happened .","depth":3},{"id":97,"text":"\" It is important to understand the factors","depth":4},{"id":98,"text":"that contributed to this tragic accident","depth":4},{"id":99,"text":"and how all stakeholders can ensure a safe and reliable rail system going forward , \"","depth":3},{"id":100,"text":"the U.S. Department of Transportation said in a statement .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":201,"left":197,"right":200,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":195,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":195,"left":158,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":106,"right":157,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":106,"left":102,"right":105,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":102,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":104,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":2,"right":103,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":157,"left":141,"right":156,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141